        "Hello,

While analyzing numpy on SonarCloud I saw what looks like an error in [`numpy/distutils/system_info.py`](https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/385575faba79b5c857112199206119bf9ac2277f/numpy/distutils/system_info.py#L293):

<img width="1590" alt="Screenshot 2020-10-07 at 14 58 09" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40498978/95333938-b856e900-08ad-11eb-8e41-23450f0fcf3a.png">


You can see the issue in SonarCloud [here](https://sonarcloud.io/project/issues?id=nicolas-harraudeau-sonarsource_numpy&issues=AXUCzxJG_fo4ewk0XE72&open=AXUCzxJG_fo4ewk0XE72).

The condition of this `if` statement will always be False because it compares a `tuple` and a string with the operator `==`. The [documentation of `platform.architecture()`](https://docs.python.org/3.8/library/platform.html#platform.architecture) explicitly says:
> Returns a tuple (bits, linkage) which contain information about the bit architecture and the linkage format used for the executable. Both values are returned as strings.

I guess the developer intended to write instead:
```
if platform.architecture()[0] == '32bit':
```

In case you have any question, suggestion or if you see a False Positive on SonarCloud you can reach out on [SonarSource community forum](https://community.sonarsource.com/).

A few notes in case you want to use SonarCloud:
